An economic model is developed to evaluate the fuel alternatives' impact on the vessel's design speed. The economic model that is incorporated in the decision tool accounts for operating revenues, voyage expenses, running expenses, and capital expenses according to the annual cash flow accounting method explained in Maritime Economics by Stopford (2013). In the following sections, all cost line items are described and elaborated such as to be able to reproduce the model. Equation 1 demonstrates how annual cash flow is calculated in the present model.3ACFvc,i=Rvc,i-Cvoyage,i-Crunning,i-Ccapital,I\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
