For the model to account for changes in future cost, the possibility of applying an escalation factor (ef) is built-in. Escalation factors are annual percentage adjustments to how the cost of a certain item develops over the years. Their application is best understood when considering inflation or technologies that become more affordable with increasing scale. In the current application, inflation is assumed constant at 2.5% per annum. The formula for determining the cost 'C' in year 'Y' is presented below.4CY= CY-1efY-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
