The required freight rate is a common financial indicator in commercial shipping. Watson defines in Practical Ship Design (Watson 1998): "The required freight rate (RFR) is that which will produce a zero NPV, i.e. the break-even rate". The present research expresses the required freight rate in $/TEU-mile. The general formula for calculating the required freight rate as found in Watson (1998). If Watson's formula for the required freight rate is subsequently adapted for the specific use case of the present research, being a container vessel transporting TEUs we get the following formula:5RFRi=∑Y=1ltCvoyage;i+Crunning;i+Ccapital;i1+rY∑Y=1ltTEUAnnual,i.dAnnual,i\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
